import React, {Component} from 'react' import styled, {ThemeProvider} from 'styled-components' import { Audio, Box, Column, Img, MastheadTitle, MastheadSubtitle, PlayButton, Spacer, Subtitle, Table, Td, Text, Thead, Th, Tr, Title, Section, Wrapper } from '../../components' import {Masthead} from '../../containers' import PlayImg from '../../assets/images/play.svg' // audio import cdnUrl from '../../../src/config/secrets.js' const cdn = cdnUrl.cdn import source from '../../../src/data/spanish/level2/vocab.js' function SpanishLevel2(props) { return ( Level Two - Spanish{' '} Learn the Spanish alphabet
Greetings{' '} Spanish 2
Consonants{' '} Name{' '} Translation Play
Consonants = 'g' sound (as in{' '} k ite) = 'kk' sound (as in{' '} kite) = 'n' sound = 'd' or 't' sound = 'r' or 'l' sound = 'm' sound = 'b' or 'p' sound = 's' sound = 'ng' sound = 'j' or 'ch' sound = 'ch' sound = 'kk' sound = 't' sound = 'pp' sound = 'h' sound Vowels = 'ae' sound (as in{' '} egg) = 'e' sound (as in{' '} e gg) and sound the same. Don't be confused by the romanizations which are different.{' '} = 'a' sound (as in{' '} a ha) = 'eo' sound sound it in between the long O and short u sound. It's not a true 'u' sound like in the word 'ugly', but more like the 'o' in 'ordeal' but leaving your mouth open = 'o' sound = 'oo' or 'u' sound = 'eu' sound = 'ee' sound
Vowels with y and w Special vowels that are constructed with the y and w sounds.
= 'yu' sound = 'ya' sound = 'yeo' sound = 'yo' sound = 'ye' sound{' '} = 'yi' sound{' '} = 'wu' sound = 'wa' sound = 'weo' sound = 'wo' sound = 'we' sound{' '} = 'wi' sound{' '}
Grammar
New Vocabulary
New Phrases Greetings and Goodbyes Annyeong ha seyo, anyeonghigeseyo yo du bun My name is nice to meet you Thank You You're Welcome
Special Notes sounds like an 'l' at the beginning of a word sounds like a 'd' in the middle of a word while surrounded by verbs. When you have a word that contains a syllable starting with and that syllable is preceded by a or being the batchim consonant of that syllable, the will actually sound like a . (dinosaur) pronounced gong-nyong
) } export default SpanishLevel2
